comments.body:
I've done this in QA.  A couple things:

1. In catalog-alma-qa there's no way to login to see your bookmarks, except via the link that appears in the "temporary bookmarks" piece. The page you get at that point has barcode login - is that still a thing?
2. The bookmark count is right, but after clicking you get no bookmarks. This is because it does a solr search on all the stored IDs, which are now wrong. I think we can patch the barcode controller to replace all those IDs with alma equivalents and this feature should work fine.
3. Search history doesn't migrate. This is because searches aren't attaching to users, it's just displaying the searches from your session. I don't know if this is a bug or I'm misunderstanding the feature or what. Are there still "saved searches"? In any case, it might be that these are just lost.

There's a link to log in on both the bookmarks page and the saved searches page.

I think searches from the session should become saved searches if you log in.

Nah I think saved searches have been broken since 2019:

```ruby
#<Search id: 76058995, query_params: {"utf8"=>"", "f1"=>"all_fields", "op2"=>"AND", "f2"=>"author", "op3"=>"AND", "f3"=>"title", "f_inclusive"=>{"advanced_location_s"=>["rcpph"]}, "range"=>{"pub_date_start_sort"=>{"begin"=>"", "end"=>""}}, "sort"=>"score desc, pub_date_start_sort desc, title_sort asc", "search_field"=>"advanced", "controller"=>"catalog", "action"=>"index"}, user_id: 3, user_type: "User", created_at: "2019-07-16 20:06:58", updated_at: "2019-07-18 17:39:41">
```

That's the most recent saved search attached to a user.
